  "text": "In order to solve (CC-MPOC) computationally, it is possible to exploit e.g. problemtailored SQP-methods, cf. [CITATION_1] ; [CITATION_2] , or relaxation schemes, see [CITATION_3] for an overview. Here, we focus on the well-known global relaxation approach of Scholtes, see [CITATION_4] , which turned out to be numerical efficiency in comparison with other relaxation methods, see [CITATION_5] . For some parameter t ≥ 0, we consider the nonlinear surrogate problem",
